<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,905,2010]" pageId="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,470,1049,1074]" pageId="3">Description of female.</emphasis>
Length from apex of rostrum to apex of elytra: 
<quantity box="[1048,1186,1049,1074]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.9" metricValueMax="5.3" metricValueMin="4.5" pageId="3" unit="mm" value="4.9" valueMax="5.3" valueMin="4.5">4.5–5.3 mm</quantity>
; length from apex of pronotum to apex of elytra: 
<quantity box="[464,602,1085,1110]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" metricValueMax="4.1" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="3" unit="mm" value="3.8" valueMax="4.1" valueMin="3.5">3.5–4.1 mm</quantity>
; width across humeral calli: 0.8–1.0 mm. Habitus: 
<figureCitation box="[1174,1240,1085,1110]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[180,1388,203,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[170,1400,195,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 18. Stereodermus spp. 1 – 8, S. micropterus Mantilleri, sp. nov., ♀: 1, paratype, habitus; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, head, lateral view; 4, left antenna; 5, abdomen; 6, abdominal tergum (mn, metanotum; hw, hind wing; TII, tergite II; TVI, tergite VI; TVII, tergite VII); 7, tergite VIII; 8, coxites and spermatheca. 9 – 18, S. platycornis Mantilleri, sp. nov.: 9, ♀ paratype, habitus; 10, head and prothorax, dorsal view; 11, head, lateral view; 12, right antenna; 13, ♂, abdomen; 14, ♀, sternite VII; 15, ♂, sternites VIII – IX; 16, tegmen; 17, penis; 18, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246756/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,905,2010]" box="[199,524,1121,1146]" pageId="3">Dark brown-red, legs lighter.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,905,2010]" pageId="3">
Head (
<figureCitation box="[273,340,1157,1182]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[180,1388,203,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[170,1400,195,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 18. Stereodermus spp. 1 – 8, S. micropterus Mantilleri, sp. nov., ♀: 1, paratype, habitus; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, head, lateral view; 4, left antenna; 5, abdomen; 6, abdominal tergum (mn, metanotum; hw, hind wing; TII, tergite II; TVI, tergite VI; TVII, tergite VII); 7, tergite VIII; 8, coxites and spermatheca. 9 – 18, S. platycornis Mantilleri, sp. nov.: 9, ♀ paratype, habitus; 10, head and prothorax, dorsal view; 11, head, lateral view; 12, right antenna; 13, ♂, abdomen; 14, ♀, sternite VII; 15, ♂, sternites VIII – IX; 16, tegmen; 17, penis; 18, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246756/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) much broader than long, not punctate, more or less concave or notched at base, with longitudinal groove. Temples almost indistinct, glabrous. Metarostrum and mesorostrum grooved. Sides of metarostrum (
<figureCitation box="[1361,1427,1193,1218]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[180,1388,203,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[170,1400,195,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 18. Stereodermus spp. 1 – 8, S. micropterus Mantilleri, sp. nov., ♀: 1, paratype, habitus; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, head, lateral view; 4, left antenna; 5, abdomen; 6, abdominal tergum (mn, metanotum; hw, hind wing; TII, tergite II; TVI, tergite VI; TVII, tergite VII); 7, tergite VIII; 8, coxites and spermatheca. 9 – 18, S. platycornis Mantilleri, sp. nov.: 9, ♀ paratype, habitus; 10, head and prothorax, dorsal view; 11, head, lateral view; 12, right antenna; 13, ♂, abdomen; 14, ♀, sternite VII; 15, ♂, sternites VIII – IX; 16, tegmen; 17, penis; 18, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246756/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) with 2–3 weak sensorial pores. Prorostrum very elongate but slightly shorter than head, metarostrum and mesorostrum together. Venter of head and metarostrum glabrous, base with shallow thin groove. Venter of mesorostrum glabrous, with two paramedian grooves. Antennal scape almost as broad as long, hardly longer than antennomeres 2–3 together (
<figureCitation box="[470,540,1337,1362]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[180,1388,203,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[170,1400,195,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 18. Stereodermus spp. 1 – 8, S. micropterus Mantilleri, sp. nov., ♀: 1, paratype, habitus; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, head, lateral view; 4, left antenna; 5, abdomen; 6, abdominal tergum (mn, metanotum; hw, hind wing; TII, tergite II; TVI, tergite VI; TVII, tergite VII); 7, tergite VIII; 8, coxites and spermatheca. 9 – 18, S. platycornis Mantilleri, sp. nov.: 9, ♀ paratype, habitus; 10, head and prothorax, dorsal view; 11, head, lateral view; 12, right antenna; 13, ♂, abdomen; 14, ♀, sternite VII; 15, ♂, sternites VIII – IX; 16, tegmen; 17, penis; 18, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246756/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); articles 2–8 very short, much broader than long, with row of short thick setae; articles 9–10 cylindrical, broader than long; article 11 shorter than articles 9–10 together.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,905,2010]" pageId="3">
Pronotum not punctate, microreticulate, glabrous, with longitudinal median groove deeper at base, connected to collar constriction. Prosternum depressed behind collar constriction. Prosternellum distinct. Metasternum not grooved, with very shallow punctures on sides. Elytra fused together (but suture still distinct), glabrous, shiny, base straight with humeral calli not strongly marked; interstriae 3–10 quite deep, striae 5–8 with large punctures. Metanotum (
<figureCitation box="[300,367,1553,1578]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[180,1388,203,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[170,1400,195,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 18. Stereodermus spp. 1 – 8, S. micropterus Mantilleri, sp. nov., ♀: 1, paratype, habitus; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, head, lateral view; 4, left antenna; 5, abdomen; 6, abdominal tergum (mn, metanotum; hw, hind wing; TII, tergite II; TVI, tergite VI; TVII, tergite VII); 7, tergite VIII; 8, coxites and spermatheca. 9 – 18, S. platycornis Mantilleri, sp. nov.: 9, ♀ paratype, habitus; 10, head and prothorax, dorsal view; 11, head, lateral view; 12, right antenna; 13, ♂, abdomen; 14, ♀, sternite VII; 15, ♂, sternites VIII – IX; 16, tegmen; 17, penis; 18, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246756/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) almost completely membranous; hind wings (
<figureCitation box="[924,991,1553,1578]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[180,1388,203,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[170,1400,195,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 18. Stereodermus spp. 1 – 8, S. micropterus Mantilleri, sp. nov., ♀: 1, paratype, habitus; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, head, lateral view; 4, left antenna; 5, abdomen; 6, abdominal tergum (mn, metanotum; hw, hind wing; TII, tergite II; TVI, tergite VI; TVII, tergite VII); 7, tergite VIII; 8, coxites and spermatheca. 9 – 18, S. platycornis Mantilleri, sp. nov.: 9, ♀ paratype, habitus; 10, head and prothorax, dorsal view; 11, head, lateral view; 12, right antenna; 13, ♂, abdomen; 14, ♀, sternite VII; 15, ♂, sternites VIII – IX; 16, tegmen; 17, penis; 18, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246756/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) vestigial. Femora unarmed, glabrous except few short thick setae at base of metafemora. First metatarsal segment shorter than segments 2–3 together.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,905,2010]" pageId="3">
Sternites III–IV (
<figureCitation box="[390,457,1625,1650]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[180,1388,203,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[170,1400,195,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 18. Stereodermus spp. 1 – 8, S. micropterus Mantilleri, sp. nov., ♀: 1, paratype, habitus; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, head, lateral view; 4, left antenna; 5, abdomen; 6, abdominal tergum (mn, metanotum; hw, hind wing; TII, tergite II; TVI, tergite VI; TVII, tergite VII); 7, tergite VIII; 8, coxites and spermatheca. 9 – 18, S. platycornis Mantilleri, sp. nov.: 9, ♀ paratype, habitus; 10, head and prothorax, dorsal view; 11, head, lateral view; 12, right antenna; 13, ♂, abdomen; 14, ♀, sternite VII; 15, ♂, sternites VIII – IX; 16, tegmen; 17, penis; 18, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246756/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) almost glabrous, hardly punctate, with longitudinal depression. Sternites V–VI almost glabrous with very shallow punctures. Sternite VII with few setae and large shallow punctures, weakly depressed on each sides at apex. Tergites II–V membranous, VI weakly sclerotized (
<figureCitation box="[989,1057,1697,1722]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[180,1388,203,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[170,1400,195,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 18. Stereodermus spp. 1 – 8, S. micropterus Mantilleri, sp. nov., ♀: 1, paratype, habitus; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, head, lateral view; 4, left antenna; 5, abdomen; 6, abdominal tergum (mn, metanotum; hw, hind wing; TII, tergite II; TVI, tergite VI; TVII, tergite VII); 7, tergite VIII; 8, coxites and spermatheca. 9 – 18, S. platycornis Mantilleri, sp. nov.: 9, ♀ paratype, habitus; 10, head and prothorax, dorsal view; 11, head, lateral view; 12, right antenna; 13, ♂, abdomen; 14, ♀, sternite VII; 15, ♂, sternites VIII – IX; 16, tegmen; 17, penis; 18, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246756/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Tergite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[1231,1298,1697,1722]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[180,1388,203,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[170,1400,195,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 18. Stereodermus spp. 1 – 8, S. micropterus Mantilleri, sp. nov., ♀: 1, paratype, habitus; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, head, lateral view; 4, left antenna; 5, abdomen; 6, abdominal tergum (mn, metanotum; hw, hind wing; TII, tergite II; TVI, tergite VI; TVII, tergite VII); 7, tergite VIII; 8, coxites and spermatheca. 9 – 18, S. platycornis Mantilleri, sp. nov.: 9, ♀ paratype, habitus; 10, head and prothorax, dorsal view; 11, head, lateral view; 12, right antenna; 13, ♂, abdomen; 14, ♀, sternite VII; 15, ♂, sternites VIII – IX; 16, tegmen; 17, penis; 18, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246756/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) of peculiar shape, without apical teeth but with deep median notch. Coxites and styli: 
<figureCitation box="[1028,1096,1733,1758]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[180,1388,203,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[170,1400,195,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 18. Stereodermus spp. 1 – 8, S. micropterus Mantilleri, sp. nov., ♀: 1, paratype, habitus; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, head, lateral view; 4, left antenna; 5, abdomen; 6, abdominal tergum (mn, metanotum; hw, hind wing; TII, tergite II; TVI, tergite VI; TVII, tergite VII); 7, tergite VIII; 8, coxites and spermatheca. 9 – 18, S. platycornis Mantilleri, sp. nov.: 9, ♀ paratype, habitus; 10, head and prothorax, dorsal view; 11, head, lateral view; 12, right antenna; 13, ♂, abdomen; 14, ♀, sternite VII; 15, ♂, sternites VIII – IX; 16, tegmen; 17, penis; 18, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246756/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
. Spermatheca (
<figureCitation box="[1275,1341,1733,1758]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[180,1388,203,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[170,1400,195,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 18. Stereodermus spp. 1 – 8, S. micropterus Mantilleri, sp. nov., ♀: 1, paratype, habitus; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, head, lateral view; 4, left antenna; 5, abdomen; 6, abdominal tergum (mn, metanotum; hw, hind wing; TII, tergite II; TVI, tergite VI; TVII, tergite VII); 7, tergite VIII; 8, coxites and spermatheca. 9 – 18, S. platycornis Mantilleri, sp. nov.: 9, ♀ paratype, habitus; 10, head and prothorax, dorsal view; 11, head, lateral view; 12, right antenna; 13, ♂, abdomen; 14, ♀, sternite VII; 15, ♂, sternites VIII – IX; 16, tegmen; 17, penis; 18, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246756/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) sickleshaped, without basal bulge.
</paragraph>
